article.description: Dantez Walton had 18 points as Northern Kentucky narrowly defeated Ball State 59-57 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Walton scores 18 to lead N. Kentucky over Ball St. 59-57
article.linkText: Walton scores 18 to lead N. Kentucky over Ball St. 59-57
article.story: MUNCIE, Ind. -- Dantez Walton had 18 points as Northern Kentucky narrowly defeated Ball State 59-57 on Wednesday night. Trevon Faulkner had 17 points and six rebounds for Northern Kentucky (4-1). Tyler Sharpe added 10 points. Faulkner and Adham Eleeda made four free throws in the final 40 seconds to help Northern Kentucky, which has won three straight games, hold off the Cardinals. Kyle Mallers had 17 points for Ball State (3-2). Ishmael El-Amin added 13 points. K.J. Walton had 12 points and nine rebounds. Tahjai Teague chipped in 10 points while grabbing 12 rebounds. Northern Kentucky takes on Texas Southern at home on Saturday. Ball St. takes on Howard at home on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- Elements of this story were generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
